Linux Basic commands

command syntax linux


Basic command 
>List the files and directories
ls 
 option
  -l => Long listing
  -d => directories
      - ls -d */
  -t => modifed time first
  -r => resverse
  -h => size in human readable
  -1 => show data in single column
  -R => recursive files in the folder


 Wildcards in commands
  - ls anand*
  - ls [1-4][1-3]apples 
  - ls files.*


  cd
	>change direcotry
		- cd <path> 
		- cd  ~ will route to your home directory
		- cd  - will route to your previous path

-Copy a directory
 cp -r <source_dir> <destination_dir>
 
 option
    -v verbose
    -p preserve the time stamp and

  move the file or direcory
    mv <source_file> <destination_file>
